Unix command
 - Rename                               -> mv old_filename new_filename
 - Remove folder content                -> rm -r <directory>
 - Remove Empty folder                  -> rmdir <directory>

Mac
 - Show hidden files                    -> shift + cmd + .
 - Move windows                         -> fn + ctrl + arrow key
 - Open folder in new terminal tab      -> cmd + .
 - End of page                          -> fn + right arrow
 - Home/Top of page                     -> fn + left arrow
 - Force close                          -> opt + cmd + esc
 - Move Paste                           -> opt + cmd + v

Vim
 - Replace first in line                -> :s/pattern/replacement/
   - Replace in file                    -> :%s///
   - Replace all                        -> :s///g
 - Edit next matching                   -> cgn
 - Find text                            -> /pattern
   - Find next                          -> n
   - Find previous                      -> N
 - Copy to clipboard                    -> "+y
 - Navigate paragraphs                  -> { or }
 - Delete around paragraph              -> dap
 - delete till paragraph                -> d{ or d}
 - visual block (multiple cursor)       -> ctrl v
 - Record action                        -> q + <character>
 - Replay action                        -> @ + <saved character>

Intellij
 - Reformat file                        -> opt + cmd + l
 - Refactor imports                     -> ctrl + opt + o

Git
 - git config --global alias.<alias> '<Command>'
 - Rename branch                        -> git branch -m <new-branch-name>
 - Restore chages                       -> git restore <file/.>
 - Cherry pick commits                  -> git cherry-pick --no-commit <commit-sha>
 - Set upstream                         -> git b -u origin/<branch-name>
 - git reset to origin                  -> git reset --hard origin/<branch-name>
 - git show commit diff                 -> git show <commit-hash>

Kubernetes:
 - kubectl get pods -n <namespace>
 - kubectl config get-contexts
 - kubectl config use-context <name>
 - kubectl describe pod <podname> -n dhp-shared-services